<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60178">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60178</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaelumyodi>Kaelum Yodi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(11/25/02 1:14:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7926.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   EQOA</span><hr size=1> EverQuest Online Adventures has nothing at all in common with EQPC, other than having similar classes/races.  In EQOA, all characters are designed to be able to solo 100% of the time.  Mages not only nuke, but also melee.  If you don't melee, you'll be one dead mage.  You don't really need clerics or chanters at all.  You eat food to increase your health, and you drink to increase your mana.  And all inventory slots can stack to 100 items w/o any weight restriction.<br>
<br>
The way they handle deaths is a million times better than the way its handled in EQPC.  For one, you go into exp debt, you don't lose exp.  This means there is no possible way to lose your level, and thus you don't have to remem your spells each time you die.  Until your debt is paid in full, 50% of your exp goes to pay off the debt.  Debt can build up from multiple deaths.<br>
<br>
At the moment, pets in EQOA are basically backup.  You can't sent a pet off to attack anything, it will just assist you when you get attacked.  There is a pet attack command, but you have to be in melee range of the mob for the pet to attack, so its useless.  SOE can't decide how they want pets to work yet, they are still getting input from all the beta testers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=7926.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=7926.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=7926.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7926.topic&index=28><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.threadControl?topicID=7926.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7926.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7926.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump 